name: NamedItem
description: Represents a defined name for a range of cells or value. Names can be primitive named objects (as seen in the type below), range object, reference to a range. This object can be used to obtain range object associated with names.

properties.name: type
properties.description: Indicates what type of reference is associated with the name.

properties.name: value
properties.description: Represents the formula that the name is defined to refer to. E.g. =Sheet14!$B$2:$H$12, =4.75, etc.

properties.name: visible
properties.description: Specifies whether the object is visible or not.

methods.name: getRange
methods.description: Returns the range object that is associated with the name. Throws an exception if the named item's type is not a range.

methods.name: load
methods.description: Fills the proxy object created in JavaScript layer with property and object values specified in the parameter.

parameters.name: param
parameters.description: Accepts parameter and relationship names as delimited string or an array. Or, provide [loadOption](loadoption.md) object.
